                The India Gate (formerly known as All India War Memorial) is a war memorial 
                located near the Kartavya path on the eastern edge of the "ceremonial axis" of 
                New Delhi, formerly called Rajpath. It stands as a memorial to 84,000 soldiers of 
                the Indian Army who died between 1914 and 1921 in the First World War, in France, 
                Flanders, Mesopotamia, Persia, East Africa, Gallipoli and...<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India_Gate">read more</a>
